RINEX broadcast-ephemeris -> ECEF interop fixtures: provenance & licenses
=========================================================================

This directory holds an external-oracle cross-validation of kshana's RINEX
broadcast-ephemeris satellite-position evaluation against RTKLIB, an independent
IS-GPS-200 / Galileo OS SIS ICD / BeiDou OS SIS ICD implementation. The pinned
reference vectors (rinex_ecef_reference.txt) are REAL RTKLIB output, produced by
compiling RTKLIB from C source and running it offline, so CI needs no runtime
RTKLIB. See generate_rinex_sp3_interop_reference.sh to reproduce.

Files
-----
- rtklib_driver.c
    Our (AGPL-3.0-only) C driver. Calls RTKLIB readrnx() + eph2pos().
- generate_rinex_sp3_interop_reference.sh
    Our (AGPL-3.0-only) regeneration script.
- brdc_multignss_slice.rnx
    Vendored multi-GNSS RINEX 3.05 navigation slice (input; see below).
    SHA-256: 17339ab508d301dbbbad4dc48fd6ec8678d7a71d1024da7b4f54dea94b28ec27
- rinex_ecef_reference.txt
    Pinned RTKLIB eph2pos ECEF positions (the committed reference vectors).


